    en: "An Individual Taxpayer Identification Number (ITIN) is a 9-digit number issued by the IRS to people who must file federal taxes but are not eligible for a Social Security Number. The application is IRS Form W-7. ITINs are used by undocumented workers, certain visa holders, foreign students, and dependents claimed on a U.S. tax return who do not qualify for an SSN. An ITIN does not authorize work in the U.S. and does not change immigration status. ITINs allow the holder to file taxes, claim certain tax credits, open a bank account at most institutions, and report income properly."
